baseline_groups.claim_summary: Higher UI benefits (log weekly benefit amount) increase log unemployment rates in a state-year-age panel with state, year, and part fixed effects.
baseline_groups.notes: Pooled specification with state+year+part FE, demographics and education controls, clustered at state. Coefficient=-0.476. Most robustness specs branch from this model.

baseline_groups.claim_summary: The unemployment elasticity with respect to UI benefits varies systematically across age groups, with differential responsiveness by age.
baseline_groups.notes: Age-interaction baseline with lnwba x age group dummies. Base coefficient=0.508 for youngest group. No robustness specs directly test a comparable age-interaction model.

global_notes: Spec search focused on CPS aggregate panel analysis. 52 specs total. One spec (subsample_nonwhite) has missing SE. Sign discrepancy between baselines warrants attention.
